          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The incident beam current was limited to less than 30",
                "nA as monitored by a Faraday cup. During the",
                "experiment, the chamber was kept at a high vacuum of",
                "less than 3.0E-5 Pa."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A thin solid target Ni/TiTx/Al2O3 was prepared by the",
                "conventional hydrogenation method, the atomic ratios",
                "of Ti, T and H is 10:8:1, and the atomic thickness of",
                "the TiTx layer is about 3.5E17 atoms/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An Au/Si surface barrier detector was",
                "employed to detect the backscattered ions at a",
                "laboratory angle of 165 deg, with a solid angle of",
                "0.00183 sr. At a laboratory angle of 30 deg, another",
                "Au/Si surface barrier detector with a solid angle of",
                "0.00246 sr was placed to detect the elastic recoil",
                "spectrum. The angular resolution of both detectors",
                "were approximately +-0.5 deg and the energy",
                "resolution of the detection system was about 30 keV",
                "for 12C ions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The relative determination method."
              ]
            }
